SUMMARY:Concurrent Exhibitions at List Gallery
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['List Gallery']\\nCategory: Reception\\nJoin us 
 for two concurrent exhibitions at the List Gallery: Paper Journeys: Pop-u
 p Books and Constructions by Colette Fu and Views of Travel\, Reverie\, 
 and Repose: Selected East Asian Works from the Swarthmore College Art Coll
 ection. Together\, these exhibitions explore current and historical East 
 Asian works and themes\, such as culture and identity\, travel and its tr
 ansformations\, and the importance of diverse narratives. Paper Journeys
  features mixed-media works by Colette Fu\, a Philadelphia-based artist
  who is known for her paper constructions that explore her Nuosu Yi anc
 estry and the cultural traditions of diverse ethnic minority groups in Chi
 na. Views of Travel\, Reverie\, and Repose features works from Swarthmor
 e's College Art Collection and highlights concerns explored by East Asi
 an artists from the 14th century to the mid-twentieth century. These int
 errelated exhibitions were co-curated and organized by Andrea Packard\,
  Director of the Swarthmore College Art Collection and Curator of the List
  Gallery\; Sara Hesdon Buehler\, Art Collection Manager\; and Susan Eberha
 rd\, Visiting Assistant Professor\, Art History.The exhibitions will be on
  view in the List Gallery from March 3 through April 19\, 2026.Colette Fu 
 will give a talk about her work on Thursday\, March 19 at 4:30 PM in the L
 ang Performing Arts Center Cinema\; an opening reception will follow in th
 e List Gallery from 5:30 to 7:00 PM.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarth
 more.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1369684981
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1369684981
CATEGORIES:Reception
END:VEVENT
