SUMMARY:Building Trauma-Informed Campus Support for Survivors (Immigrant-In
 formed)
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['SGO'\, 'Swatties for Immigrant Rights']\\nCateg
 ory: Student Activity (no alcohol)\\nThis is a collaboration with the Nati
 onalities Service Center (NSC)\,  a Philadelphia nonprofit that provides 
 trauma-informed services to immigrant and refugee communities\, including 
 survivors of violence and other forms of trauma. The event delivers a trau
 ma-informed campus support workshop that equips students\, faculty\, and s
 taff with practical tools for responding to disclosures of violence and co
 nnecting survivors to appropriate resources. This programming is especiall
 y timely given the recent increase in Title IX–related concerns across c
 ampus and the corresponding need for clearer\, more survivor-centered supp
 ort practices in everyday campus spaces. While the workshop is open to all
  survivors of violence\, it includes an immigrant-informed lens to address
  cultural and structural barriers (e.g.\, language access\, stigma\, and f
 ear of systems) that can shape help-seeking and safety.\\nDetails: https:/
 /swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D13806072
 96
LOCATION:McCabe LibLab\, Full Space\, Conference Room
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1380607296
CATEGORIES:Student Activity (no alcohol)
END:VEVENT
