SUMMARY:Exhibition: Artists' Books: Pop-Up!
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Swarthmore College Libraries']\\nCategory: Exhi
 bit\\nThis exhibition features innovative and diverse pop-up books from th
 e Book Arts & Private Press Collection. The works on view demonstrate how 
 contemporary book artists are using the book structure to inform their art
 . Of special interest are works by Philadelphia-based artist Colette Fu\, 
 whose work explores her Nuosu Yi ancestry and the cultural traditions of d
 iverse ethnic minority communities in China. Fu will be teaching an intr
 oduction to pop-up book structures in McCabe Library on March 28.\\nDetai
 ls: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid
 %3D1368371819
LOCATION:McCabe Library Atrium Exhibits
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1368371819
CATEGORIES:Exhibit
END:VEVENT
