SUMMARY:What is the Translation Workshop (class in Fall 2026)?
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Russian'\, 'Linguistics'\, 'Modern Languages an
 d Literatures']\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nA meeting to learn 
 about the Translation Workshop\, scheduled to be taught by Professor Sibe
 lan Forrester on Wednesdays from 1:15-4:00 (with a snack break) this fall.
  The class will combine 1) reading and discussing works on translation his
 tory from two millennia and chapters on translation theory\, 2) in-class e
 xercises including experiments with various AI interventions\, and 3) work
 shopping translations in progress in small groups. Any language with a wr
 itten tradition may be used\, or multiple languages if a student knows mo
 re\; students should have\, at a minimum\, intermediate reading proficienc
 y (or else access to a VERY patient native or proficient speaker) - about 
 the equivalent of finishing an 004 (fourth-semester) language class at Swa
 rthmore College. How can a professor grade translations from ANY language?
  - The grade will be based on the difference between the rough draft and t
 he final draft\, as well as contributions to discussion and contributions 
 to the small group work. The outcome will be both some entertaining biling
 ual (multilingual) readings at the end of the fall and a portfolio of work
  that could then be submitted for publication. Students may register for 
 LING 070 (in which case the final portfolio must include a paper on an iss
 ue from Linguistics alongside translations that illustrate that issue)\, L
 ITR 070R (final portfolio may be a paper plus related translations OR a l
 onger set of translations)\, or RUSS 070 (final portfolio may involve a pa
 per plus translations or only translations\, but must be working from Russ
 ian). Questions\, or can't make it in person? Contact Professor Forreste
 r at sforres1@swarthmore.edu>.\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.e
 du/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1385106219
LOCATION:Kohlberg Room 114 - Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1385106219
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
