SUMMARY:HEARD External Speaker Series - Andrew Thompson
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ['Lang Center for Civic & Social Responsil']\\nCa
 tegory: Lecture/Panel Discussion\\nThe Healthy\, Equitable\, and Responsiv
 e Democracy (HEARD) Initiative welcomes Prof. Andrew Thompson to present h
 is latest work\, "Reducing Anti-Democratic Support by Reducing Racial Thre
 at." Thompson is an Assistant Professor of Political Science at the Univer
 sity of Pennsylvania. Broadly\, his research studies how racial demographi
 c changes alter political perceptions and democratic commitments. The even
 t is open to all Swarthmore faculty\, staff\, and students.\\nDetails: htt
 ps://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1367
 358690
LOCATION:Kohlberg Room 116 - Flexible Classroom
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1367358690
