SUMMARY:The Harvard School of Meaning- Centered Medical Anthropology: Refle
 ctions After 50 Years
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Lecture/Panel Di
 scussion\\nThe Harvard School of Meaning-Centered Medical Anthropology: Re
 flections After 50 Years WHEN: Tuesday\, April 21\, 2026\, 4:30 pm WHERE:
  Science Center 101   Why should meaning-centered Medical Anthropology ma
 tter for undergraduates\, social scientists\, and educated people globally
 ? This talk uses the story of Harvard's five decades of medical anthropolo
 gical teaching\, research and practice to illustrate why a meaning-centere
 d approach to experience is so vital for our times. That approach creates 
 a framework for the practical application of wisdom derived from the human
  sciences and puts it to work to reimagine our social condition and develo
 p more availing approaches and practices. This talk is dedicated to a form
 er student and leader of the Harvard program: Paul Farmer\, whose brillian
 ce and moral passion informed our emphasis on accompaniment\, human rights
 \, and integration of the moral\, the emotional and the practical.\\nDetai
 ls: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid
 %3D1382232485
LOCATION:Science Center Room 101- Chang Hou Hall Tiered Classroom\, Science
  Center Room 101- Chang Hou Hall Lobby
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1382232485
CATEGORIES:Lecture/Panel Discussion
END:VEVENT
