SUMMARY:“What’s in a (Building’s) Name?”
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Meeting\\n“Wha
 t’s in a (Building’s) Name?”  Scheuer Room\, Kohlberg Hall April 22
 \, 4:30-6:00 p.m.   Lisa Alvarez-Cohen\, Vice Provost for Academic Planni
 ng\, UC Berkeley Kim Cassidy ’85\, H’25\, Ninth President\, Bryn Mawr 
 College Cat Norris\, Chair\, Renaming Task Force and Moderator     Desc
 ription: This is the third in a series of events on the renaming of Old Sc
 ience Hall.  Lisa Alvarez-Cohen\, an environmental engineer whose researc
 h focuses on the application of microbiological processes for the eliminat
 ion of environmental contaminants\, was named Berkeley’s vice provost fo
 r academic planning in 2018. Last year\, Berkeley chose an Indigenous name
  for a campus building and consulted with Indigenous people in the process
 .   Kimberly Wright Cassidy ’85\, H’25\, joined Bryn Mawr’s psychol
 ogy faculty in 1993 and served as its ninth president from 2013-2024. Duri
 ng her tenure as president\, she oversaw the renaming of Bryn Mawr’s lib
 rary.     Cat Norris is Associate Dean of the Faculty for Academic Prog
 rams and Research and an associate professor of psychology. She joined Sw
 arthmore’s faculty in 2013.First event:April 1 – Anatomy of a Shadow E
 conomy: Body Snatching and the Making of American Medicine Second event:A
 pril 15 – Old Science Hall Renaming Task Force: Our Charge and Process\,
  Community Survey Results\, and Q&AFourth event:April 29 – A Talk by Jer
 emy Johnson\, Cultural Education Director\, Delaware Tribe of Indians\\nDe
 tails: https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26even
 tid%3D1382122033
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1382122033
CATEGORIES:Meeting
END:VEVENT
