SUMMARY:A Talk by Jeremy Johnson\, Cultural Education Director\, Delaware T
 ribe of Indians
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["Provost's Office"]\\nCategory: Meeting\\nA Talk
  by Jeremy Johnson\, Cultural Education Director\, Delaware Tribe of India
 ns  Scheuer Room\, Kohlberg Hall April 29\, 4:30-6:00 p.m.   Description
 : This is the fourth and final event in a series on the renaming of Old Sc
 ience Hall.   Jeremy Johnson is the cultural education director of the De
 laware Tribe of Indians\, based in Bartlesville\, Okla. He is Lenape\, Abs
 entee Shawnee\, and Peoria. Prior to his current role\, he served as assis
 tant chief of the Delaware Tribe. A lifelong educator\, he is committed to
  preserving and revitalizing Lenape culture and language for the future ge
 nerations of his tribe.    All events are sponsored by the Swarthmore Co
 llege President’s Office.Past events:First event:April 1 – Anatomy of 
 a Shadow Economy: Body Snatching and the Making of American Medicine Seco
 nd event:April 15 – Old Science Hall Renaming Task Force: Our Charge and
  Process\, Community Survey Results\, and Q&AThird event:April 22 – “W
 hat’s in a (Building’s) Name?”\\nDetails: https://swatcentral.swarth
 more.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%3D1382122034
URL:https://swatcentral.swarthmore.edu/?trumbaEmbed=view%3Devent%26eventid%
 3D1382122034
