DTSTAMP:20260406T115327Z
DTSTART:20260604T153000Z
DTEND:20260604T173000Z
SUMMARY:Garnet Day
DESCRIPTION:Organized by: ["President's Office"]\\nCategory: Reception\\nWe
 lcome the long-awaited springtime with music and dance!  This Garnet Day\
 , stop by the beautiful new Arts Plaza behind Martin Hall between 10:30 a.
 m. and 12:30 p.m. to enjoy musical and dance performances from our talente
 d student artists. There will also be treats from The Chilly Banana food t
 ruck (vegan options available) and the chance to talk to folks from Get Ou
 t the Vote\, the Office of Sustainability\, the Swarthmore Coalition on We
 ll-Being\, Student Disability Services\, and the Inclusive Excellence Fell
 ows Initiatives. Garnet Day Springtime Music and Dance Celebration Arts Pl
 aza\, Behind Martin Hall Thursday\, April 2 10:30 a.m. – 12:30 p.m. Rain
  location Lang Concert Hall and Lobby We hope you can join us in celebrati
 ng the warmer weather and our talented community members. As always\, reme
 mber to wear your Swarthmore gear to show your spirit! Congratulations to 
 last month's Garnet Day Guessing Game winners: Charlotte Dustin ‘29 (fir
 st place)\, Kat Matekovic (second place)\, and Amanda Whitbred\, Communica
